comments[3]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-19T15:37:44.474Z",maintainer-agent,"Evidence: fence coverage contract now includes relationships/**/*.jsonl under new pm-relationship driver (eventId union + consecutive sequence renumbering so the strict store loader accepts merged streams); pm schema add-type/remove-type auto-refresh the installed fence (merge_fence_refreshed) or emit merge_fence_not_installed hint; validate storage_integrity audits committed fence vs active schema folders and warns validate_merge_fence_drift with exact missing/stale lines (warn-only when data is intact). Manual sandbox: driver renumbered 1,2 + 1,2 -> 1,2,3; schema add-type Spike refreshed fence; drift detected after out-of-band edit and cleared by pm merge install. Specs: merge-safety (16), schema-command (67), validate-command (91) green."
  "2026-07-19T16:09:06.411Z",codex-wide-sdk-20260719,"Final merge-fence implementation: the installed fence assigns pm-relationship to every tracker JSONL path via .agents/pm/**/*.jsonl, then applies the more-specific history/*.jsonl pm-history override. This protects custom RelationshipEventStore relative paths and future schema folders without weakening hash-chain history handling. Focused tests cover install/repair/audit, arbitrary custom paths, relationship union/renumbering, timestamp ties, missing optional timestamps, malformed streams, and the real driver artifact. Full coverage is 100/100/100/100."
  "2026-07-19T16:38:23.135Z",codex-wide-sdk-20260719,"Greptile pre-push review 2b371c5d-ceb0-4948-8d0a-1b403891b2c5 identified two merge edge cases. Accepted: automatic fence refresh resolves the repository from the absolute pmRoot, proven while process.cwd() is a different git checkout; relationship timestamp ties now keep ours-before-theirs while stable sorting preserves each side's original append order. The pmRoot-derived git root made the prior outside-root branch impossible, so it was removed rather than artificially covered. Focused 25-test regression set and full 5,976-test 100/100/100/100 gate pass."
learnings[2]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-19T15:38:31.609Z",maintainer-agent,"Strict-sequence JSONL stores (relationship events validate sequence === version+1 at load) can never be text-union-merged: any merge driver for them must renumber the merged stream consecutively, not just union lines. The pm-history driver was NOT reusable here — history chains re-anchor hashes, relationship streams renumber sequences; different invariants, different drivers."
  "2026-07-19T16:09:07.324Z",codex-wide-sdk-20260719,"A relationship event store is customizable below the tracker root, so merge safety must fence the artifact class by general JSONL coverage with a specific history override, not by assuming a fixed relationships directory. Git attributes last-match specificity preserves the distinct history driver."
